                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> RIEVAL (Abbey of). <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Paulinus</forename>, 
                  canon of the church of St. Peter of York</persName>
                        </persName>,
                  quit-claims to the <orgName key="org_103003">church and monks of St. Mary, Rievall</orgName>, all the claim he has
                  upon the bounds (divisas) of <placeName key="place_103391">Welleburn</placeName> near his land of 
                  <placeName key="place_103283">Nagelt[on]</placeName> and <placeName key="place_103407">Wimbelt[on]</placeName>, viz.
                  the bounds contained in the charters of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> de
                   <surname>Molbrai</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>Nigel</forename> his son</persName>; 
                  which bounds, the same Roger with his men and neighbours (vicinis) perambulated and affirmed by oath
                  to be the right bounds of Wellebr', because the said Thomas's men falsely suggested to him that they
                  belonged to his land of Nagelt[on] and Wimbelt[on]; and being unwilling unjustly to vex
                  the said monks, he therefore, after full enquiry, makes this quit-claim, which is attested by 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Paulini</surname>, his nephew</persName>,
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Hereford</surname> his cousin</persName>, and 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> son of <persName>
                              <forename>Rainer</forename>
                              <surname>Puer</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>.
                  (<origDate notBefore="1190" notAfter="1200" precision="low">c. 1190-1200</origDate>.) 
                  . </p>
                  </msItem>
